%N A209882 Smallest k>=0 such that n*(n+1)-(2*k+1) and n*(n+1)+(2*k+1) are both noncomposite numbers, or -1 if no such k exists.
%e A209882 a(1) = 0 because 1*(1+1)-(2*0+1)=1 and 1*(1+1)+(2*0+1)=3 are both noncomposite numbers.
%e A209882 a(2) = 0 because 2*(2+1)-(2*0+1)=5 and 2*(2+1)+(2*0+1)=7 are both noncomposite numbers.
%e A209882 a(3) = 0 because 3*(3+1)-(2*0+1)=11 and 3*(3+1)+(2*0+1)=13 are both noncomposite numbers.
%e A209882 a(4) = 1 because 4*(4+1)-(2*1+1)=17 and 4*(4+1)+(2*1+1)=23 are both noncomposite numbers.
%o A209882 (PARI) isc(c) = (c>1) && !isprime(c);
